Retail trading algorithms frequently fail because they try to force static rules onto dynamic markets so to solve this, I took an institutional approach to the engineering process. 
By reviewing academic papers on high-frequency mean reversion and volatility scaling, I was able to base this model on proven mathematical concepts rather than guesswork. 
The Bhatti momentum filter and Z-score execution parameters used in this codebase are direct practical applications of the research found in this paper: [https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=6087107]
